  <title translate="true">GNC: Ghost-Node Correction Package Pane</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">GNC: Ghost-Node Correction Package Pane</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The Ghost-Node Correction package is used to specify the ghost nodes in MODFLOW 6 DISV models. The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">GNC: Ghost-Node Correction Package</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane is on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Packages_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Packages and Programs</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box under </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Flow_Packages" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Flow Packages</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The user must specify whether to use an implicit or explicit formulation for ghost nodes. See the MODFLOW 6 documentation for further details. The locations and weights for ghost nodes are assigned automatically by ModelMuse. The implicit option may make the solution less stable but should result if a more accurate solution if the model does converge.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The Ghost-Node Correction package can not be used with the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="NPF_Node_Property_Flow_Package" anchor="XT3D" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">XT3D</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> option in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="NPF_Node_Property_Flow_Package" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Node Property Flow</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> package.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">In ModelMuse, all other information for the Ghost-Node Correction package are determined automatically when the user switches to a </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Discretization_with_Vertices_D" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">DISV</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> grid.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
